So much of what I do relies on me to hermit myself away to my studio and struggle with staying focused enough to produce enough to just exist amongst this life, that I tend to forget to enjoy a lot of it. Thank the gods for @kara.perry.photography suggesting shoots and busting her butt to put them together for us because these “work events” really breathe life into me again. 
I don’t even realize I’ve been holding my breath for weeks/months until I’m there surrounded by friends and getting to see what Ive been working on come to life.
 These are the days I do & will cherish most throughout my years 
Thank you so much for making this happen my sweet sweet sweetie babes

THIS MONDAY 
Big ole bra restock but with a twist ‼️
Now that I finally have some huge help getting these bras made (thank you @amescutandsew !!!) 
I am going to attempt to offer up having the option of choosing your strap preference, the options being the new single strap design or the older double strap with fabric tab design.
.
I love them both and am excited to finally be able to give you the choice between two, and as so many of you reach out regularly asking if the double strap will ever make a come back, now is the time! 
There will be a price difference for the double strap as the double strap option takes me almost 3 times as long as the new single strap style.
I am attempting to add this all to the bra listings to keep it a simple breezy check out as usual, hopefully will have it all figured out by Monday.

Two announcements!
First up is that Today is the day, Bra Restock Day and not your typical restock this one will include a choose your own strap finish customization option and it goes live at 3pm EST ❤️‍🔥
I’d like to say this will be a forever option buttttt I can’t say that :) this is very much a trial run!
So if you have been missing & itching for the double straps this is the perfect opportunity to snatch one up.

Next up is the coveted William Morris collection is currently in the works and while I don’t have an exact date for you yet it will be early June for sure for sure, so turn on post notifications if you don’t want to miss the announcement for that shop update!

Raffle to help our mom get on her feet
My sister and I have joined forces to try and raise some money to help our Mom. None of us are used to asking for help and I know we all are navigating these troubled times together, so thank you for reading and giving us the space to be outside of ourselves in this moment

Here's the situation: Our mom has been diagnosed with early on-set alzheimer's and has been waiting on/fighting for disability for 2.5 years now. She lost her small apartment in St.Petersburg, FL last July due to the Air BnB take over and could not find an affordable place to live anywhere.  Luckily right now she currently receives 1k from ssi & a friend in Hudson who owns a house let our mom move in for $500 a month, unfortunately that leaves mom with only $500 a month to pay for bills, food, dog food, emergencies, etc. Chloe and I implement her finances as much as we can but neither one of us is anywhere close to a position where we can be doing so without it directly impacting both of our lives in a big way 
So she recently claimed bankruptcy to help clear her of some debts... yet, she often has a negative account balance when her next check is still weeks away. My mom has always lived frugally, worked hard and never really wanted or asked for much, to be met with this diagnosis and what it entails without financial support has been trying to put it mildly.

We know this is not a long term fix, but we're hoping to raise enough money to get debt collectors off our backs, and provide some income relief for a few months while we figure out our next steps for her   Our mom is such a sweet, kind, compassionate person & artist see her art here (@mp.verbrugghe) who hasn't deserved much of the struggles she has had over her lifetime. Chloe and I are doing everything in our power to get our mom on her feet and into a stable and workable living situation.
We greatly appreciate your help.  The tickets are $10 an entry and available on either one of our websites, links in profiles, there is no limit to how many times you enter. Names to be chosen on Friday June 23rd.

Phew, I feel like I’ve been holding my breath all month. Afraid to go forward afraid to look behind me and no real energy for the present. Turning 39 was harder than I thought it would be, not because of the number but the self reflection time was/is more intense than any of the other birthdays so far…. I think?
The who am I’s the how am I here’s the where I want to be’s. I get overloaded and over stimulated unfortunately very easy which causes me to freeze and fall.
But then this morning co star with all its beautiful insightfulness reminded me with 
“When you feel stuck remember that your present situation isn’t your final destination” and that felt good so, passing that on to you maybe if you might need to hear a simple truth this morning too 
.
